    "assignee": null,
    "body": "The Physics simulation seem to treat Open Doors, Steps and half blocks as full blocks.",
    "closed_at": "2013-01-11T02:46:00Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "It's a known issue, since the physics are not based on Notch's (yet?).  I haven't done any work with the actual code for the physics, but to add to the list:\n\nSince the collision is incomplete, to temporarily avoid issues with the server correcting positions, partial blocks are treated as full blocks.  Doors, slabs, ladders, cake, redstone repeaters (I believe), are all full blocks in the physics, and fences are treated as two blocks.\n\nLiquids and slow sand also do not slow the player.",
